hopped.org/getshopped-news/wp-e-commerce-3-8-10-beta/";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}s:8:"comments";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:73:"http://getshopped.org/getshopped-news/wp-e-commerce-3-8-10-beta/#comments";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}s:7:"pubDate";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:31:"Tue, 19 Feb 2013 20:53:40 +0000";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}s:8:"category";a:3:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:10:"Developers";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}i:1;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:15:"GetShopped News";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}i:2;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:20:"WP e-Commerce Plugin";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}s:4:"guid";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:31:"http://getshopped.org/?p=302802";s:7:"attribs";a:1:{s:0:"";a:1:{s:11:"isPermaLink";s:5:"false";}}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}s:11:"description";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:525:"<p>We&#8217;re excited to announce that WP e-Commerce 3.8.10 beta is now ready for testing. This is the first whole release where our cycle is managed completely on GitHub. Our roadmap as well as development schedule were published on our GitHub wiki page, and reality turned out to be different from what we expected when we [...]</p><p>The post <a href="http://getshopped.org/getshopped-news/wp-e-commerce-3-8-10-beta/">WP e-Commerce 3.8.10 beta</a> appeared first on <a href="http://getshopped.org">GetShopped.org</a>.</p>";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}}s:32:"http://purl.org/dc/elements/1.1/";a:1:{s:7:"creator";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:8:"Gary Cao";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}}s:40:"http://purl.org/rss/1.0/modules/content/";a:1:{s:7:"encoded";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:8712:"<p>We&#8217;re excited to announce that WP e-Commerce 3.8.10 beta is now ready for testing.</p>\n<p>This is the first whole release where our cycle is <a href="https://github.com/wp-e-commerce/wp-e-commerce">managed completely on GitHub</a>. Our <a href="https://github.com/wp-e-commerce/wp-e-commerce/wiki/Roadmap">roadmap</a> as well as <a href="https://github.com/wp-e-commerce/wp-e-commerce/wiki/Development-Schedule">development schedule</a> were published on our GitHub wiki page, and reality turned out to be different from what we expected when we wrote those documents.</p>\n<p>First of all, we received overwhelmingly positive feedback from the dev community, evident in the number of pull requests, bug reports and discussions. This whole release cycle has been 90% community driven and we&#8217;re very proud to have such support.</p>\n<p>Second, at the beginning of the cycle, we planned to have 2 major features, and 3 underlying architectural changes for this release, all within the span of 2 months. This turned out to be unrealistic. Even though we have many contributors, by the time we originally scheduled for beta (February 17th), we completed one feature, one architectural change, and a lot of bug fixes. So we&#8217;re faced with two choices: stick to the original dates and re-schedule the other tasks to the next release (3.8.11), or make amends to the schedule and delay the final release.</p>\n<p>Eventually, we decided to stick to the original schedule and follow <a href="http://wordpress.org/about/philosophy/#deadlines">WordPress.org philosophy on deadlines</a>.</p>\n<style type="text/css">\nblockquote#this {padding: 0 0 0 15px; margin: 20px 0 !important; border-left: 5px solid #cccccc; text-align:left; font-family: Helvetica, Arial, sans-serif; font-size: 14px; line-height: 26px; color: #444; width: 100%;}\nblockquote#this p {font-size: 16px !important; font-weight: normal !important; line-height: 26px !important; font-family: Helvetica, Arial, sans-serif !important; color: #444 !important; margin-top:0 !important;}\n</style>\n<blockquote id="this"><p><strong>Deadlines Are Not Arbitrary</strong><br />\nDeadlines are not arbitrary, they’re a promise we make to ourselves and our users that helps us rein in the endless possibilities of things that could be a part of every release. We aspire to release three major versions a year because through trial and error we’ve found that to be a good balance between getting cool stuff in each release and but not too much that we end up breaking more than we add.</p>\n<p>Good deadlines almost always make you trim something from a release. This is not a bad thing, it’s what they’re supposed to do.</p></blockquote>\n<p>This might end up a small release, much smaller than 3.8.8 or 3.8.9, but we&#8217;re pretty sure you won&#8217;t be any less happy with it. Each of our upcoming release cycles will also be small and quick like this one. We figured by doing things this way, users get new features, improvement and bug fixes much faster and more frequently.</p>\n<p><strong>What&#8217;s new in 3.8.10-beta</strong></p>\n<p>We have completely revamped the UI for managing Coupons in the admin area. Below you can find several screenshots of this new UI and the full changelog.</p>\n\n<a class="thickbox" rel="attached-to-302802" href=''http://getshopped.org/getshopped-news/wp-e-commerce-3-8-10-beta/attachment/screen-shot-2013-02-19-at-11-09-36-pm/'' title=''Main Coupon Screen''><img width="150" height="150" src="http://getshopped.org/wp-content/uploads/2013/02/Screen-Shot-2013-02-19-at-11.09.36-PM-150x150.png" class="attachment-thumbnail" alt="Main Coupon Screen" title="Main Coupon Screen" /></a>\n<a class="thickbox" rel="attached-to-302802" href=''http://getshopped.org/getshopped-news/wp-e-commerce-3-8-10-beta/attachment/screen-shot-2013-02-19-at-11-10-01-pm/'' title=''New Coupon Screen''><img width="150" height="150" src="http://getshopped.org/wp-content/uploads/2013/02/Screen-Shot-2013-02-19-at-11.10.01-PM-150x150.png" class="attachment-thumbnail" alt="New Coupon Screen" title="New Coupon Screen" /></a>\n<a class="thickbox" rel="attached-to-302802" href=''http://getshopped.org/getshopped-news/wp-e-commerce-3-8-10-beta/attachment/screen-shot-2013-02-19-at-11-10-34-pm/'' title=''Edit Coupon Screen''><img width="150" height="150" src="http://getshopped.org/wp-content/uploads/2013/02/Screen-Shot-2013-02-19-at-11.10.34-PM-150x150.png" class="attachment-thumbnail" alt="Edit Coupon Screen" title="Edit Coupon Screen" /></a>\n\n<pre>* New: Coupon UI is revamped.\r\n* New: [Shipwire] Addition of Shipping Services, Economy, Plus &amp; Premium.\r\n* Change: After filling out a registration form, the user is logged in.\r\n* Change: Limit quantity of individual products that can be added to the cart.\r\n  Default value is filterable.\r\n* Change: Remove FPDF which is not used any more.\r\n* Change: Return cart item messages as key =&gt; value array rather than HTML.\r\n* Change: Variation table class orderby to ''menu_order title''\r\n* Change: When displaying packing slip, form data should be output in the same\r\n  order as that of checkout page.\r\n* Fix: "you save" prices are not correct on variations with a value over 1000\r\n* Fix: Cart widget missing closing &lt;/div&gt; tag.\r\n* Fix: Display the "You save" price as a currency, not just a raw unformatted\r\n  number\r\n* Fix: Ensure all variations are deleted when deleting a product.\r\n* Fix: Foreign characters are not displayed correctly in packing slip.\r\n* Fix: Improved performance with variations.\r\n* Fix: JavaScript error when no variations exist in admin.\r\n* Fix: Make sure Add / Edit Product page respects decimal and thousands\r\n  separators set in Settings-&gt;Store-&gt;General.\r\n* Fix: Manual / Test Payment instructions don''t appear on transaction results\r\n  page and email.\r\n* Fix: Only print Google Analytics scripts on transaction results footer\r\n* Fix: PHP Warnings when bulk editing variations.\r\n* Fix: Prevent old paypal express from hijacking new paypal express callback.\r\n* Fix: Product category pages don''t respect pagination and sort order settings.\r\n* Fix: Re-generate products pages'' IDs after plugin reactivation.\r\n* Fix: Refactor user account page\r\n* Fix: SQL IN error in wpsc_populate_also_bought_list().\r\n* Fix: Switching a purchase log status to "Closed Order" doesn''t reduce stocks.\r\n* Fix: WPML compatibility\r\n* Fix: Wrong cache set for checkout form data.\r\n* Fix: split() deprecation notice in PHP 5.3+\r\n* Fix: stripslashes issues when duplicating products.</pre>\n<p><strong>How to download and test</strong></p>\n<p>Before you get too excited and rush to download 3.8.10-beta, please understand that <strong>this beta package is strictly for testing purposes</strong>. We&#8217;ve tested as much as we can and squashed as many bugs as we encounter. But we cannot be completely certain that it&#8217;s absolutely bug free, considering the vast combination of server configurations out there. That&#8217;s exactly the reason why we have beta releases, so that you can help us test and make sure that your site will work perfectly with the official release.</p>\n<p><strong><a href="http://downloads.wordpress.org/plugin/wp-e-commerce.3.8.10-beta.zip">» Click here to download WP e-Commerce 3.8.10-beta here «</a></strong></p>\n<p>Then extract the downloaded package, and upload the resulting folder to your server&#8217;s <code>wp-content/plugins</code> directory, overwriting existing files.</p>\n<p><strong>I think I found a bug. What should I do?</strong></p>\n<p>First you need to determine whether it&#8217;s a security issue, or just a plain simple bug. Please read the following documents as it contains detailed instructions on how to report issues on our bug tracker. It only takes 5 minutes but would be extremely helpful!</p>\n<ul>\n<li><a href="https://github.com/wp-e-commerce/wp-e-commerce/wiki/Reporting-a-security-issue">Reporting a security issue</a></li>\n<li><a href="https://github.com/wp-e-commerce/wp-e-commerce/wiki/Creating-issue-tickets">Creating issue tickets</a></li>\n</ul>\n<p><strong>Note to contributors</strong><br />\nWe&#8217;ll have a list of contributors to this release up when the 3.8.10 is officially released. We will use the name that you use for your commits (usually configured by <code>git config --global user.name</code>). We will also link to the website that you specify on your GitHub profile. If that&#8217;s not available, we&#8217;ll link to your GitHub profile instead. So take the time to prepare your GitHub profile!</p>\n<p>The post <a href="http://getshopped.org/getshopped-news/wp-e-commerce-3-8-10-beta/">WP e-Commerce 3.8.10 beta</a> appeared first on <a href="http://getshopped.org">GetShopped.org</a>.</p>";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}}s:36:"http://wellformedweb.org/CommentAPI/";a:1:{s:10:"commentRss";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:69:"http://getshopped.org/getshopped-news/wp-e-commerce-3-8-10-beta/feed/";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}}s:38:"http://purl.org/rss/1.0/modules/slash/";a:1:{s:8:"comments";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:1:"0";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}}}}i:1;a:6:{s:4:"data";s:41:"\n		\n		\n		\n		\n		\n				\n\n		\n		\n			\n			\n		\n		";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";s:5:"child";a:5:{s:0:"";a:7:{s:5:"title";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:31:"WPEC 3.8.10 in T-minus 25 days!";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}s:4:"link";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:74:"http://getshopped.org/wp-e-commerce-plugin/wpec-3-8-10-in-t-minus-25-days/";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}s:8:"comments";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:83:"http://getshopped.org/wp-e-commerce-plugin/wpec-3-8-10-in-t-minus-25-days/#comments";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}s:7:"pubDate";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:31:"Sat, 02 Feb 2013 21:46:22 +0000";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}s:8:"category";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:20:"WP e-Commerce Plugin";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}s:4:"guid";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:31:"http://getshopped.org/?p=301479";s:7:"attribs";a:1:{s:0:"";a:1:{s:11:"isPermaLink";s:5:"false";}}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}s:11:"description";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:557:"<p>Hi all, Justin Sainton here.  If you don&#8217;t know me &#8211; I&#8217;m one of the two lead developers for the WP E-Commerce project.  Gary, our other fearless lead developer, is focusing heavily on internal projects and other exciting upcoming happenings. That means I get the pleasure of leading the 3.8.10 release. There will be a [...]</p><p>The post <a href="http://getshopped.org/wp-e-commerce-plugin/wpec-3-8-10-in-t-minus-25-days/">WPEC 3.8.10 in T-minus 25 days!</a> appeared first on <a href="http://getshopped.org">GetShopped.org</a>.</p>";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}}s:32:"http://purl.org/dc/elements/1.1/";a:1:{s:7:"creator";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:14:"Justin Sainton";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}}s:40:"http://purl.org/rss/1.0/modules/content/";a:1:{s:7:"encoded";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:6454:"<p>Hi all,</p>\n<p>Justin Sainton here.  If you don&#8217;t know me &#8211; I&#8217;m one of the two lead developers for the WP E-Commerce project.  Gary, our other fearless lead developer, is focusing heavily on internal projects and other exciting upcoming happenings.</p>\n<p>That means I get the pleasure of leading the 3.8.10 release.</p>\n<p><strong>There will be a dev IRC chat for this release on <a href="http://everytimezone.com/#2013-2-8,540,6be">Friday, February 8 at 21:00 UTC</a>  in #wpec-dev  on freenode </strong>(click the link for that time in your timezone).</p>\n<p>This release is really special for a few reasons -</p>\n<ol>\n<li>It&#8217;s the first release that we&#8217;re using <a href="https://github.com/wp-e-commerce/WP-e-Commerce">GitHub</a> for.  If you haven&#8217;t noticed, we migrated from Google Code to GitHub in the last month, and the response from the developer community has been absolutely astounding.</li>\n<li>After the behemoth that was 3.8.9, we&#8217;re excited to have an incredibly targeted, focused release cycle on 3.8.10.  There are just a few things we&#8217;re focusing on improving and introducing.  More on that in a bit.</li>\n<li>Lastly, it&#8217;s special because it&#8217;s the first release I&#8217;m leading.  Color me honored.</li>\n</ol>\n<div>\n<p><strong>There will be a dev IRC chat for this release on <a href="http://everytimezone.com/#2013-2-8,540,6be">Friday, February 8 at 21:00 UTC</a>  in #wpec-dev  on freenode </strong>(click the link for that time in your timezone).</p>\n</div>\n<p>All that said, here&#8217;s the feature list for 3.8.10 &#8211; these are things we&#8217;d like to focus on as a community and see improved or introduced in 3.8.10.</p>\n<ul>\n<li><strong>Media</strong> &#8211; WordPress 3.5 introduced an incredible media experience.  We want to explore how we can leverage this new UI for an incredible product creation experience for shop owners.  Naturally, we&#8217;ll take care to ensure the previous media handling works as expected for users who haven&#8217;t upgraded to 3.5 yet.  Aside from the fact that it&#8217;s crazy not to upgrade, they&#8217;ll be missing out on any new and special features introduced to the new UI.</li>\n<li><strong>Coupons</strong> &#8211; It&#8217;s been a little while since our Coupon UI has been given any love.  Thanks to some pretty incredible efforts by Pippin Williamson, a new Coupon UI is taking shape in a fabulous way.  We&#8217;ll see this introduced (along with some minor coding enhancements as well) in 3.8.10.</li>\n<li><strong>Javascript</strong> &#8211; WP E-Commerce has been around since before Twitter, Gangnam style or Facebook ads.  We&#8217;ve got a long road of legacy cruft and technical debt to pay off.  One of the most obvious and painful places this is true is in our javascript.  Gary has done a brilliant job of overhauling much of the admin-facing javascript, we&#8217;re going to take a big whack at the front-end javascript in this release.  I&#8217;m personally handling this aspect of the release, and I&#8217;m incredibly excited about it.</li>\n<li><strong>Variations - </strong>One of the most common problems I hear about is performance issues when people have TONS of variations.  We have an incredibly robust variations system that works for most people and allows you to do some really cool things.  We&#8217;re going to take a look at making iterative, meaningful performance enhancements this release.  I believe, that as of our last major release, we have the best variations UX of any plugin out there.  That said, we still have a lot of room to grow in the UX department, so any other UX/UI tweaking we can do here to make it a better experience overall will be considered.  The key word for this part of the release is &#8216;iterative&#8217;.</li>\n<li><strong>Cart Meta API</strong> &#8211; With every major release, we try to focus on an area or two that simply need an API architecture overhaul.  You&#8217;ve seen it with our Settings page class, our Countries class and our Purchase Logs class (several others as well) &#8211; all of which are a breeze to work with.  For this release, I&#8217;d like to focus on making it easy to create and interact with cart item meta.  While it may sound vague, if this is built properly, it allows nearly endless customization options that are currently only possible through clunky, hacky work-around methods.</li>\n</ul>\n<p>Beyond that, any bugfixes, incremental performance enhancements, documentation improvements etc. that we can get it &#8211; all the better.  I know what you&#8217;re thinking, &#8220;My goodness, Justin, that&#8217;s a ton of work for a single release that&#8217;s going out in less than four weeks!&#8221;  You are right.  But we have a secret weapon.</p>\n<p><strong>YOU.</strong></p>\n<p>The move to <a href="https://github.com/wp-e-commerce/WP-e-Commerce">GitHub</a> has shown us something amazing &#8211; there is an incredible community of developers simply itching to give back to WP E-Commerce.  It&#8217;s humbling and exciting.  This marks the first release where we&#8217;re on a community development platform that allows us to leverage the very thing that makes WPEC amazing &#8211; our community.  Utilizing GitHub, already this month we&#8217;ve seen a record number of contributions from non-core developers.  New issues that are incredibly helpful, great pull requests almost daily.  The momentum only continues to build and we&#8217;re incredibly stoked about it.</p>\n<p><strong>There will be a dev IRC chat for this release on <a href="http://everytimezone.com/#2013-2-8,540,6be">Friday, February 8 at 21:00 UTC</a>  in #wpec-dev  on freenode </strong>(click the link for that time in your timezone).</p>\n<p>Come to the dev chat prepared and ready to pitch in, whatever that looks like.  Maybe you can pitch in 30 minutes a week, maybe you have several hours you can devote to something.  Perhaps you have some great client project that <em>needs </em>an API refresh or a bug fixed.  Come to the dev chat &#8211; if we all pitch in together, we can continue to make WPEC the best, most popular, free and open-source e-commerce plugin out there.</p>\n<p>The post <a href="http://getshopped.org/wp-e-commerce-plugin/wpec-3-8-10-in-t-minus-25-days/">WPEC 3.8.10 in T-minus 25 days!</a> appeared first on <a href="http://getshopped.org">GetShopped.org</a>.</p>";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}}s:36:"http://wellformedweb.org/CommentAPI/";a:1:{s:10:"commentRss";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:79:"http://getshopped.org/wp-e-commerce-plugin/wpec-3-8-10-in-t-minus-25-days/feed/";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}}s:38:"http://purl.org/rss/1.0/modules/slash/";a:1:{s:8:"comments";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:2:"22";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}}}}i:2;a:6:{s:4:"data";s:59:"\n		\n		\n		\n		\n		\n				\n		\n		\n		\n		\n		\n		\n\n		\n		\n			\n			\n		\n		";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";s:5:"child";a:5:{s:0:"";a:7:{s:5:"title";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:43:"WP e-Commerce Proud to Partner with iThemes";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}s:4:"link";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:84:"http://getshopped.org/themes-and-design/wp-e-commerce-proud-to-partner-with-ithemes/";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}s:8:"comments";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:93:"http://getshopped.org/themes-and-design/wp-e-commerce-proud-to-partner-with-ithemes/#comments";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}s:7:"pubDate";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:31:"Fri, 21 Dec 2012 02:20:46 +0000";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}s:8:"category";a:7:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:14:"Premium Themes";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}i:1;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:17:"Themes and Design";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}i:2;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:20:"WP e-Commerce Plugin";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}i:3;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:5:"depot";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}i:4;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:7:"iThemes";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}i:5;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:6:"market";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}i:6;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:6:"Themes";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}s:4:"guid";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:31:"http://getshopped.org/?p=297855";s:7:"attribs";a:1:{s:0:"";a:1:{s:11:"isPermaLink";s:5:"false";}}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}s:11:"description";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:552:"<p>The team at WP e-Commerce is proud to announce a new partnership with iThemes. We love the team at iThemes personally, but the reason we really admire them is their ability to make WordPress easy: themes that just do what you ask, plugins that don&#8217;t demand you be a developer. (You may notice we recommend [...]</p><p>The post <a href="http://getshopped.org/themes-and-design/wp-e-commerce-proud-to-partner-with-ithemes/">WP e-Commerce Proud to Partner with iThemes</a> appeared first on <a href="http://getshopped.org">GetShopped.org</a>.</p>";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}}s:32:"http://purl.org/dc/elements/1.1/";a:1:{s:7:"creator";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:10:"amandablum";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}}s:40:"http://purl.org/rss/1.0/modules/content/";a:1:{s:7:"encoded";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:2559:"<p>The team at <a title="WP e-Commerce Plugin Theme Partners" href="http://www.getshopped.org">WP e-Commerce</a> is proud to announce a new partnership with <a href="http://ithemes.com/">iThemes</a>. We love the team at iThemes personally, but the reason we really admire them is their ability to make WordPress easy: themes that just do what you ask, <a href="http://ithemes.com/find/plugins/">plugins</a> that don&#8217;t demand you be a developer. (You may notice we recommend <a href="http://ithemes.com/purchase/backupbuddy/">Backup Buddy</a> for your site backups whenever WPEC is upgraded).</p>\n<p>In particular, we love iThemes themes for WP e-Commerce. they&#8217;re easy to use and turn WP e-Commerce into a slick, clean, customizable shop in a flash. You&#8217;ll notice you can now purchase <a href="http://getshopped.org/premium-upgrades/premium-theme-2/">premium themes</a> in addition to plugins. We&#8217;re launching with two themes: <a href="http://getshopped.org/premium-upgrades/premium-theme-2/depot-theme-for-wp-e-commerce-by-ithemes/">Depot</a> and <a href="http://getshopped.org/premium-upgrades/premium-theme-2/market-theme-for-wp-e-commerce-by-ithemes/">Market</a>.<br />\n<a href="http://getshopped.org/wp-content/uploads/2012/12/depot-shopp-400x290.jpg"><img class="alignleft size-full wp-image-297678" title="depot-shopp-400x290" src="http://getshopped.org/wp-content/uploads/2012/12/depot-shopp-400x290.jpg" alt="" width="400" height="290" /></a><a href="http://getshopped.org/wp-content/uploads/2012/12/market-400x290.jpg"><img class="alignleft size-full wp-image-297675" title="market-400x290" src="http://getshopped.org/wp-content/uploads/2012/12/market-400x290.jpg" alt="" width="400" height="290" /></a></p>\n<div style="clear: both;"></div>\n<p>Both feature multiple page templates, a beautiful design that pushes products to the forefront. Depot is a clean theme with a focus on marketing, ideal for clothes or retail or anything you can dream up. Market is a sleek and smart theme that allows Grid View to really shine, while allowing customers to visualize products in a sensible way.</p>\n<p>The team at WP e-Commerce is working hard to bring new add ons to you, including a wealth of theming options in the new year. We&#8217;re thrilled to launch with a partner as experienced as iThemes.</p>\n<p>The post <a href="http://getshopped.org/themes-and-design/wp-e-commerce-proud-to-partner-with-ithemes/">WP e-Commerce Proud to Partner with iThemes</a> appeared first on <a href="http://getshopped.org">GetShopped.org</a>.</p>";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}}s:36:"http://wellformedweb.org/CommentAPI/";a:1:{s:10:"commentRss";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:89:"http://getshopped.org/themes-and-design/wp-e-commerce-proud-to-partner-with-ithemes/feed/";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}}s:38:"http://purl.org/rss/1.0/modules/slash/";a:1:{s:8:"comments";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:1:"1";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}}}}i:3;a:6:{s:4:"data";s:56:"\n		\n		\n		\n		\n		\n				\n		\n		\n		\n		\n		\n\n		\n		\n			\n			\n		\n		";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";s:5:"child";a:5:{s:0:"";a:7:{s:5:"title";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:58:"WP e-Commerce 3.8.9.4 is now compatible with WordPress 3.5";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}s:4:"link";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:97:"http://getshopped.org/getshopped-news/wp-e-commerce-3-8-9-4-is-now-compatible-with-wordpress-3-5/";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}s:8:"comments";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:106:"http://getshopped.org/getshopped-news/wp-e-commerce-3-8-9-4-is-now-compatible-with-wordpress-3-5/#comments";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}s:7:"pubDate";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:31:"Wed, 12 Dec 2012 17:25:35 +0000";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}s:8:"category";a:6:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:15:"GetShopped News";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}i:1;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:20:"WP e-Commerce Plugin";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}i:2;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:7:"3.8.9.4";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}i:3;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:14:"blank checkout";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}i:4;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:13:"media manager";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}i:5;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:8:"shipwire";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}s:4:"guid";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:31:"http://getshopped.org/?p=297037";s:7:"attribs";a:1:{s:0:"";a:1:{s:11:"isPermaLink";s:5:"false";}}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}s:11:"description";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:604:"<p>WP e-Commerce 3.8.9.4 is now available for download. In this release, we fixed some major issues with certain hosting configurations, especially the dreaded blank checkout page, or error when adding items to cart. We also made sure WP e-Commerce 3.8.9.4 is playing nice with WordPress 3.5. You will notice that the product edit page is [...]</p><p>The post <a href="http://getshopped.org/getshopped-news/wp-e-commerce-3-8-9-4-is-now-compatible-with-wordpress-3-5/">WP e-Commerce 3.8.9.4 is now compatible with WordPress 3.5</a> appeared first on <a href="http://getshopped.org">GetShopped.org</a>.</p>";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}}s:32:"http://purl.org/dc/elements/1.1/";a:1:{s:7:"creator";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:8:"Gary Cao";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}}s:40:"http://purl.org/rss/1.0/modules/content/";a:1:{s:7:"encoded";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:3046:"<p>WP e-Commerce 3.8.9.4 is now available for download.</p>\n<p>In this release, we fixed some major issues with certain hosting configurations, especially the dreaded blank checkout page, or error when adding items to cart. We also made sure WP e-Commerce 3.8.9.4 is playing nice with WordPress 3.5. You will notice that the product edit page is properly supporting the new media UI introduced in WordPress 3.5. It certainly makes managing product images much more pleasant.</p>\n<p>Below you can find the list of changes made in this release:</p>\n<pre>* Fix: "No shipping quotes" error is displayed when selecting\r\n"Shipping same as billing".\r\n* Fix: Avoid flooding transient data when site''s feed is being\r\n  visited by bots.\r\n* Fix: Blank Checkout page for some certain installation when\r\n  Shipping is enabled.\r\n* Fix: Can''t add to cart on some server.\r\n* Fix: Fatal error when viewing product variation iframe, because\r\n  _wp_admin_html_begin() does not exist on older WordPress versions.\r\n* Fix: MySQL error/warning in _wpsc_filter_special_widget_where().\r\n* Fix: Only show attachment fields when viewed on an edit product page.\r\n* Fix: PHP Notice in cart.class.php.\r\n* Fix: Properly escape columns in admin products page.\r\n* Fix: Purchase log''s item names are not translatable via qTranslate.\r\n* Fix: Shipping same as billing saves "State" field label as the\r\n  shipping region.\r\n* Fix: Shipwire settings are not updated.\r\n* Fix: Shipwire syncing doesn''t take into consideration products in\r\n  trash, or multiple products using the same SKUs (as in WPML)\r\n* Fix: Specials widget is empty when there are no product with variation\r\n  sales.\r\n* Fix: Variation sets are not being sorted on the front-end.\r\n* Fix: WPEC doesn''t cooperate with WP 3.5 media UI.\r\n* Fix: wpsc_pre_transaction_results filter is ignored.\r\n* Make sure admin styles are enqueued for product variations iframe in\r\n  older version of WordPress.</pre>\n<p>It is extremely important that before you upgrade to 3.8.9.4, <strong>please back up your files and databases</strong>. <a href="http://ithemes.com/member/go.php?r=27731&amp;i=l44">Backup Buddy</a> is our top choice for making backup simple and effortless.</p>\n<h5>How to upgrade</h5>\n<p>You can simply use WordPress automatic updates feature to download and install WP e-Commerce 3.8.9.4.</p>\n<p>If that doesn&#8217;t work for you, try the following steps for a manual upgrade:</p>\n<p>- <a href="http://downloads.wordpress.org/plugin/wp-e-commerce.3.8.9.4.zip">Download WP e-Commerce 3.8.9.4 from here</a> and save it to your computer.</p>\n<p>- Extract the downloaded package to a folder on your computer.</p>\n<p>- Upload the contents of that folder to this path on your server, overwriting all existing files: <code>wp-content/plugins/wp-e-commerce</code></p>\n<p>The post <a href="http://getshopped.org/getshopped-news/wp-e-commerce-3-8-9-4-is-now-compatible-with-wordpress-3-5/">WP e-Commerce 3.8.9.4 is now compatible with WordPress 3.5</a> appeared first on <a href="http://getshopped.org">GetShopped.org</a>.</p>";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}}s:36:"http://wellformedweb.org/CommentAPI/";a:1:{s:10:"commentRss";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:102:"http://getshopped.org/getshopped-news/wp-e-commerce-3-8-9-4-is-now-compatible-with-wordpress-3-5/feed/";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}}s:38:"http://purl.org/rss/1.0/modules/slash/";a:1:{s:8:"comments";a